articles.title: Low vaccine uptake among Central and Eastern European communities - CSO - The Irish Times
articles.description: CSO figures show 44 per cent of central and eastern Europeans in Ireland vaccinated
articles.content:
The uptake rate of Covid-19 vaccines in Ireland among adults from Central and Eastern Europe is less than half the rate of inoculation among Irish nationals, new figures show.
